Albizia toona

    Authority   Bailey
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
     Synonyms
   Common names red siris tree, Mackay cedar, acacia siras vermelha
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2968

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A deciduous shrub 3-5 m or a small tree reaching a
   height of 15-30 m and a diameter of up to 90 cm. The trunk is often
   short and straight. USES The timber can be used for joinery, furniture,
   and fencing. The tree is used as an ornamental. GROWING PERIOD
   Fast-growing perennial. COMMON NAMES Red siris, Acacia cedar, Mackay
   cedar. FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: Paraserianthes toona. Red siris
   occurs in coastal Queensland, Australia within the latitudinal range
   10-22Â°S at elevations between sea level and 800 m. It can be found on
   sites that varies from gentle slopes in coastal lowlands and foothills,
   along stream and river banks to high, rugged ranges and rocky
   hillsides. It is nitrogen-fixing. (pH estimated by the compiler).

   Sources
   SOURCES (A. toona Bailey)
   Turnbull J 1986 pp 220-221 [TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, TEXT, PH, FER, USE]

